## Hard rules
- All tables have `id` (uuid, primary key), `created_at` (timestamp UTC), `updated_at` (timestamp UTC).
- Soft deletes only: all tables have `deleted_at` (timestamp, nullable). Never hard-delete user records.
- All timestamps are stored and returned as UTC.
